<article id="post-27" class="post-27 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-building tag-building has-post-thumbnail">
	
	<a class="post-thumbnail" href="http://sustainable.ie/easca-sustainable-building-certification/">
	<img width="672" height="372" src="http://sustainable.ie/new-site/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Easca-featured-organisation.jpg" class="attachment-post-thumbnail wp-post-image" alt="Éasca was formed to promote sustainable building in Ireland and to facilitate positive change in order to mainstream sustainable building practices." />	</a>

	
	<header class="entry-header">
				<div class="entry-meta">
			<span class="cat-links"><a href="http://sustainable.ie/category/building/" title="View all posts in Building" rel="category tag">Building</a></span>
		</div>
		<h1 class="entry-title"><a href="http://sustainable.ie/easca-sustainable-building-certification/" rel="bookmark">Éasca &#8211; Sustainable Building Certification</a></h1>
		<div class="entry-meta">
			<span class="entry-date"><a href="http://sustainable.ie/easca-sustainable-building-certification/" rel="bookmark"><time class="entry-date" datetime="2014-01-13T12:49:48+00:00">January 13, 2014</time></a></span> <span class="byline"><span class="author vcard"><a class="url fn n" href="http://sustainable.ie/author/si2014-admin/" rel="author">si2014-admin</a></span></span>			<span class="comments-link"><a href="http://sustainable.ie/easca-sustainable-building-certification/#respond" title="Comment on Éasca &#8211; Sustainable Building Certification">Leave a comment</a></span>
					</div><!-- .entry-meta -->
	</header><!-- .entry-header -->

		<div class="entry-content">
		<p><a href="http://easca.ie/" target="_blank"><strong>Éasca</strong></a> was formed to promote sustainable building in Ireland and to facilitate positive change in order to mainstream sustainable building practices.</p>
<p>It brings together the most innovative private companies in the built environment. Member companies are assessed by independent assessors to ensure their products and services have a positive impact on the environment.</p>
<p><a href="http://easca.ie/" target="_blank"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-94" alt="EASCA_LOGO" src="http://sustainable.ie/new-site/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/EASCA_LOGO.png" width="300" height="104" /></a></p>
	</div><!-- .entry-content -->
	
	<footer class="entry-meta"><span class="tag-links"><a href="http://sustainable.ie/tag/building/" rel="tag">Building</a></span></footer></article><!-- #post-## -->

